org.codefx.libfx.collection.tree.navigate

Interface TreeNavigator<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements contained in the tree
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ComponentHierarchyNavigator, JComponentHierarchyNavigator, SceneGraphNavigator

    public interface TreeNavigator<E>
    A tree navigator allows to walk through a tree (i.e. a connected, directed, acyclic graph).

    This interface can be implemented to navigate arbitrary tree-like data structures without requiring them to implement a specific interface.

    The navigation relies on child nodes having some fixed order so they can be accessed via an index.

        Optional<E> getChild(E parent,

        Parameters:
        parent - a node in the tree
        childIndex - a non-negative number specifying the index of the requested child
